The value for the money is astonishing -- they are a significantly better value for your dollar just in terms of quantity than any of the fast food restaurants down the street -- and the food is always tasty.  This is especially impressive because I don't like kabobs, gyros, or shawarma that much, but I'll make an exception for this place.  My only small gripe is that I wish they gave you more pita bread with the hummus, but I'm not petty enough to subtract a star for that.  Highly recommended.

It was a stormy day, so we asked Siri a cheap place to eat and the Kabob Shack came up. We pulled up to this hole on the wall and were pleasantly surprised. The atmosphere is chill and the staff are cool people. Recommendations.... chicken and lamb gyro is absolutely delicious!! Get the jalepeno cheddar dipping sauce - you will not regret it.... not spicy, has a tiny kick, but is so deliciously creamy. Prices are reasonable ($10 for a gyro with fries... better than spending $10 for a meal at McDonalds). The cook makes EVERYTHING FRESH when you order it. This place is a hidden gem, but locals flood in to get  takeout, people call orders in and they kept getting alerts from UberEats. It's a hotspot! We are not from Williamsburg, but we pinned this location because we plan to come back again and again.

Let's start with the cashier. She was a mess to say the least. She was all over the place, and was so distracted by everything like a 5 year old kid. The cook kept telling her simple order taking steps. Second, the food is so basic and such a rip off. Such a small platter for $10 bucks!! Really? The rice was not flavorful, very basic. The kebob wasnt bad but c'mon, you're charging $10 for a kebob platter and you give me two finger length kebobs with a small platter of flavorless rice and one big quarter of an onion and tomato. SMH. This place really puts middle eastern food to shame. This is a place for inexperienced foodies to get ripped off when the food establishment doesn't even try to put a special touch on their food. Very disappointed. You really, honestly deserve one star but the cook was very nice, so you get 2. Good Luck.
